track.name: Chicago
comments: this man can do no wrong. ♥
Simply genius, ingeniously simple. This man is 62 years old and could kick ass of any random overhyped hipster one-hit band.
Keith Richards lends his guitar and vocals to a number of tracks on  the album: "Chicago", "Satisfied", "Last Leaf", and "Hell Broke Luce".

Tuesday, October 25, 2011 sees the release of Bad As Me, the first new album in seven years from the one and only Tom Waits. 
It's also the third of Tom's albums that Keith Richards has appeared on (following Rain Dogs and Bone Machine).
This song reminded me that I need to catch a train...but then I realized that I have no train to catch.
